`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
**FPS camera with R3F**: The pattern is `PerspectiveCamera makeDefault` + `ref` from drei — `makeDefault` registers it as the scene camera while the `ref` gives imperative access to update position in `useFrame`. The existing third-person `Camera.tsx` uses this same pattern, so `FPSCamera` just needs the simpler logic of `pos.y + EYE_HEIGHT` instead of spherical offsets.

**Test strategy for R3F components**: Since `@react-three/drei` and `@react-three/fiber` aren't in `transformIgnorePatterns`, they can't be parsed by Jest. The pattern (seen in `PlayerCapsule.test.ts`) is to mock them at the top and only test exported constants + component type — no rendering required.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`
