`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
**Module-level THREE.Vector3 requires mocking**: `const DEFAULT_POSITION = new THREE.Vector3(...)` runs at import time in Jest — so mocking `three` with a `Vector3` constructor spy is necessary, not optional. The mock must return an object with the methods the component calls (`copy`, `set`) or the import itself will throw.

**Eye offset is additive on ground-level position**: The player ECS `position` component stores the entity's ground contact point (y ≈ 0 for spawned entities). The camera sits at `pos.y + 1.6` — no capsule-center math needed since the ECS position is already floor-relative.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`

